SIMPLE: cursedness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cursedness
<hw>Curs"ed*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
under a curse or of being doomed to execration or to evil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wickedness; sin; cursing.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Shrewishness.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My wife's
<xex>cursedness</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curser</ent>⟦br⟧
